BLITZ 6-MAX PREFLOP STRATEGY (2NL-10NL)

SUIT CHECK: Same suit = suited (s). Different = offsuit (o).

BLITZ FACTS
- No reads, new table every hand
- 3-bets are 85%+ value
- Turn/river raises = near-nuts
- Pool overfolds to steals, underfolds to value

OPEN RAISE (2.5bb)

UTG: 77+, ATs+, KQs, AQo+
MP: 66+, ATs+, A5s-A4s, KJs+, QJs, JTs, AJo+, KQo
CO: 55+, A7s+, A5s-A2s, KTs+, QTs+, J9s+, T9s, 98s, 87s, ATo+, KJo+
BTN: 22+, A2s+, K7s+, Q8s+, J8s+, T8s+, 97s+, 86s+, 75s+, 65s, 54s, A8o+, KTo+, QTo+, JTo
SB: 44+, A2s+, K9s+, Q9s+, J9s+, T9s, 98s, 87s, A9o+, KJo+ (raise or fold)

VS SINGLE OPEN

3-bet value:
- vs UTG/MP: QQ+, AKs, AKo
- vs CO: JJ+, AQs+, AKo
- vs BTN: TT+, AQs+, AKo

3-bet bluff (BTN/SB only vs CO/BTN opens):
- A5s-A4s, K9s

Call IP:
- vs UTG/MP: JJ-88, AQs-AJs, KQs
- vs CO: TT-66, AJs-ATs, KQs-KJs, QJs, JTs
- vs BTN: 99-44, ATs-A9s, KJs-KTs, QJs-QTs, JTs, T9s, 98s, 87s

OOP (SB): 3-bet or fold. Never flat.

BB DEFENSE

vs BTN:
- 3-bet: TT+, AQs+, AKo, A5s-A4s
- Call: 99-22, AJs-A2s, KTs+, QTs+, J9s+, T8s+, 97s+, 86s+, 76s, 65s, KJo, QJo
- Fold: weak offsuit, dominated aces

vs CO:
- 3-bet: QQ+, AKs, AKo
- Call: JJ-55, AQs-A9s, KQs-KTs, QJs, JTs, T9s
- Fold: rest

vs UTG/MP:
- 3-bet: QQ+, AKs, AKo
- Call: JJ-77, AQs-ATs, KQs
- Fold: rest

VS 3-BET

4-bet/call: KK+, AKs
4-bet/fold: AKo (vs tight 3-bettor fold pre)
Call IP: QQ, JJ, AQs
Fold: TT-, AJo, KQo, suited connectors, small pairs

VS 4-BET

All-in: KK+
Call: AKs (if <100bb effective)
Fold: everything else including QQ (unless read)

AUTO-FOLD LIST

Preflop opens:
- A6o-A2o, K9o-, Q9o-, J9o-, T8o-
- Suited gappers from EP (75s, 64s, 53s)

Facing 3-bet:
- AJo, ATo, KQo, KJo, QJo
- TT-22 OOP
- All suited connectors
- 99-22 vs EP 3-bet

ADJUSTMENTS

Blinds overfold: Steal wider from CO/BTN (add K5s+, Q7s+, J8s+)
Blinds 3-bet light: Tighten steals, 4-bet wider with QQ+/AK
Villain opens too wide: 3-bet more for value (add AQo, KQs)
Villain folds to 3-bet >65%: 3-bet any two from BTN/SB

MINDSET

- You beat Blitz by folding trash and value betting made hands
- Don't bluff rivers (they call)
- Don't hero call (they have it)
- Steal blinds relentlessly with position
- When raised on turn/river, fold one pair
